!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %title Acronyms
    %style
      body { background-color: #fff; color: #000; font-family: Verdana, Arial; }
      table { border-collapse: collapse; padding: 1em 0; }
      th { border-bottom: 1px solid #000; padding: 0.5em; text-align: left; }
      td { border-top: 1px solid #000; padding: 0.5em; text-align: left; }

  %body
    %h1 Acronyms
    %p
      When working with public sector organisations, you may come across
      numerous acronyms that you do not understand. This page lists some common ones.

    %table
      %tr
        %th Acronym
        %th Meaning
      - rows.each do |row|
        - unless row.empty?
          %tr
            %td
              %strong
                - unless row[:website].to_s.empty?
                  %a{ href: row[:website] }
                    = row[:acronym]
                - else
                  = row[:acronym]
            %td
              = row[:meaning]

